<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-17155] Increase the buckets count for timer histogram</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-17155</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;EstimatedHistograms used in timers are allocated with 90 buckets, as part of &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-16760&quot; title=&quot;JMXTimer exposes attributes in inconsistent time units&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-16760&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-16760&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. It can represent the highest value of 25 seconds. The setting is not free from hitting overflow error when calculating the mean value from the histogram. We can increase the buckets count to 127 to increase the upper limit to 21,356 seconds, which just covers the range of 164 buckets prior &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-16760&quot; title=&quot;JMXTimer exposes attributes in inconsistent time units&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-16760&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-16760&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
